The rankings assessed 1 222 institutions, ranking them across 48 disciplines in five broad subject areas. The university moved up two places from 2018 to ninth position for development studies. It is the only university in the global south to feature among the top 10 for this discipline. Eight other subjects at UCT were also ranked among the top 100, including anatomy and physiology, anthropology, archaeology, architecture/built environment, education, geography, social policy and administration and sports-related subjects. 